cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with abstract algebraic logic and its application to judgment aggregation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as judgment aggregation is a problem in social choice theory, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as judgment aggregation is a game-theoretic problem. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the formalization of agendas of formulas, which can be seen as a data structure. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also less likely but possible as the paper touches on the issue of impossibility results, which is a topic in computational complexity theory.
